I'd argue Binance are net positive contributors to crypto by onboarding millions of new users. But narrative last few days has been adversarial, I want to hear a frank discussion.

Retail using binance is putting its capital at risk to these 21 validators. Retail using @Uniswap  pays a premium (in higher gas) because its native chain, Ethereum, is ORDERS of magnitude more secure and immutable. 2/3
